
This repository includes small example applications that use rs-485 port of the raspicomm.

- rs485_read
 An example application that receives 10 bytes from the rs-485 port and displays them afterwards.

 Prerequisites:
 - pyserial python module 
   make sure you have pyserial python module installed:
   1. wget https://pypi.python.org/packages/source/p/pyserial/pyserial-2.6.tar.gz
   2. tar zxvf pyserial-2.6.tar.gz
   3. cd pyserial-2.6.tar.gz
   4. sudo python setup.py install

 - git
   make sure you have git installed:
   1. sudo apt-get install git

How to use the examples:

0. use git to clone this repository 
 'git clone https://github.com/amescon/rpc-python-examples.git'

1. build the examples applications with make and run them
 
 rs485_read
  'cd rs485_read'  
  './rs485_read.py'

2. modify the code and play around with it